Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["General layout", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.8345676725896482`*^9, {3.834567833753996*^9, 3.834567851869217*^9}, {
   3.8345681718704767`*^9, 
   3.83456817923664*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"38d07d1d-045d-4658-bf6f-\
c1f8b076dd53"],

Cell["\<\
In each section below, we will create two grids. The first grid contains:
1. Compute the expected value (mu) for each distribution.
2. Compute the variance (var) for each distribution. 
3. Solve the system obtained (for params) using MofM. 
4. Substitute the sample mean and variance into params. 
The second grid contains:
5. Compute probability from 0 to 5 mg/kg. 
6. Compute 99th percentile. 
7. Compute probability from 10 to infinity. 
At the end of each block of code, we\[CloseCurlyQuote]ll clear the variables. 

At the end is a summary of all the values, in nice tables, followed by the 8 \
values requested for the project. \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.834568185556797*^9, 3.8345683291076202`*^9}, {
  3.834569721702827*^9, 3.834569747345035*^9}, {3.834569778485417*^9, 
  3.8345698146784286`*^9}, {3.834574113949073*^9, 3.8345741578268538`*^9}, {
  3.879428188825632*^9, 
  3.8794282150384483`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"46d98184-4c0b-4650-973b-\
c12b9ce6dbd4"]
}, Closed]],

